“Nobody knew there’d be a pandemic or an epidemic of this proportion,” Trump said on March 19.
A report from ABC News that was published on Wednesday may help explain the matter better — but not in a way that puts Trump in a good light.
That same source added that the Pentagon and the White House were “briefed multiple times” on the matter.
The National Security Council, the White House and other federal officials continued to receive updates on the spread of the disease throughout December, the sources elaborated.
In one poll conducted late last month, close to 6 in 10 Americans believed Trump was too slow to act when it came to the pandemic.